# Working Principle

The system continuously monitors electrical parameters using the PZEM004T sensor. The ESP32 processes these values to calculate real-time power factor.

* If power factor is within acceptable range → no action taken
* If power factor drops below threshold → capacitor banks are activated

The system dynamically switches capacitors using relays:

* 6µF, 10µF, and 15µF capacitors are combined to provide required reactive compensation

After switching:

* System waits for stabilization
* Re-evaluates power factor
* Adjusts capacitor combination if required

Additional logic:

* No-load condition → power factor forced to 1.00
* Avoids unnecessary switching

All parameters are:

* Displayed on LCD
* Sent to Blynk cloud for remote monitoring

This ensures automatic, real-time, and efficient power factor correction.
